!! Config structure

An explide config tiddler has:

|!Field |!Purpose |
|`rri.type` |Must be `explide/config` — triggers ViewTemplate integration |
|`rri.imported-plugins` |Space-separated list of plugin titles to import |
|`rri.imported-tiddlers` |Space-separated list of individual tiddler titles to import |
|`rri.output-tiddler` |Title of the tiddler to display in testcase Output (default: `Output`) |
|`description` |Human-readable description shown in the testcase |
|`rri.adhoc-tiddler:<name>` |Inline text-only tiddler content |

!! Explide data tiddlers

When you add a shadow tiddler from an imported plugin, a new tiddler is created at `<configTitle>/<shadowTitle>`. This is an "explide data" tiddler.

!! `$rri$:` field prefix remapping

Fields on explide data tiddlers that start with `$rri$:` are remapped when assembling the `$testcase`:

* `$rri$:tags` on the data tiddler becomes `tags` in the sandbox
* Regular fields (like `title`, `created`) are passed through as-is, except `title` which is stripped

This allows overriding any field without colliding with TiddlyWiki's own field handling.

!! `$genesis` pipeline

The `$data` elements inside `$testcase` are assembled via `$genesis` with three named procedures:

* `explide-data-title` — computes the sandbox title by stripping the config prefix
* `explide-names` — merges regular field names with stripped `$rri$:` field names
* `explide-values` — merges regular field values with `$rri$:` field values

!! Testcase output

The `$testcase` widget uses the `testcase-output-tiddler` attribute set to the value of `rri.output-tiddler` (defaulting to `Output`). By convention, create an ad-hoc tiddler named `Output` for the main rendered content.

!! Snapshot system

Each explide data tiddler can have a snapshot at `<dataTitle>:snapshot`. Snapshots are full copies created via `$action-createtiddler $template`. The DIFF tab compares the current data against its snapshot, or falls back to the original shadow tiddler. Restore overwrites the data tiddler from the snapshot.

!! Ad-hoc tiddlers

Fields prefixed with `rri.adhoc-tiddler:` on the config tiddler become standalone `$data` entries in the sandbox. Each becomes a simple text-only tiddler with the field suffix as its title.

!! CSS consolidation

Explide uses `rr-input-row`, `rr-input`, `rr-muted`, `rr-small`, `rr-callout-*` classes from the theme plugin. Plugin-specific styles (split layout, snapshot controls, config field label widths) are in `styles/base.css`.

